    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Classic Veracruz style and culture of Pre-Columbian art from the central-southern Gulf Coast, Mexico; named for the type site, Las Remojadas, Veracruz, which had an uninterrupted ceramic sequence from ca. 150 BCE to ca. 650 CE. The term is often applied incorrectly to ceramics of the central-southern Gulf Coast in general. Remojadas style includes distinctive pottery and hollow ceramic figurines, some of which have unusual wide smiles on triangular faces.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
